    notes: "Aggregate=3575 | easy_ft06=55 | hard_ft20=1165 | medium_ft10=930 | very_hard_swv01=1425 | This approach combines the strengths of both MILP and CP-SAT solvers. The CP-SAT solver provides a good warm-start solution quickly, which helps the MILP solver converge faster. The MILP formulation is enhanced with tight big-M constants and precedence cuts to improve solution quality. The algorithm falls back to the CP solution or greedy dispatching if MILP fails."
